Interface DataSeries<V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataSet, Iterable<V>
    All Known Subinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataSeries, AbstractSeriesView, CalcSeries, CalcSeries.Int, CalcSeries.Int.Add, CalcSeries.Int.AddSeries, CalcSeries.Int.Divide, CalcSeries.Int.DivideSeries, CalcSeries.Int.Multiply, CalcSeries.Int.MultiplySeries, CalcSeries.Int.Subtract, CalcSeries.Int.SubtractSeries, CalcSeries.Real, CalcSeries.Real.Add, CalcSeries.Real.AddSeries, CalcSeries.Real.Divide, CalcSeries.Real.DivideSeries, CalcSeries.Real.Multiply, CalcSeries.Real.MultiplySeries, CalcSeries.Real.Subtract, CalcSeries.Real.SubtractSeries, DataSeriesGeneric, DataSeriesInteger, DataSeriesReal, SeriesViewAppend, SeriesViewFunction, SeriesViewRow

    public interface DataSeries<V>
extends DataSet, Iterable<V>
    Represents a series or vector of values. Implementations typically define the type of value to store. This may be numeric or any kind of object.
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman

      • getEmptyValue

        V getEmptyValue()
        Get the value corresponding to an empty value. For floating-point numbers this is either Double.NaN or Float.NaN. For integer types it is Long.MIN_VALUE, Integer.MIN_VALUE, etc. For all other types this is usually null.

      • getBoolean

        boolean getBoolean(int index)
        Get the element at the specified index as the primitive type 'boolean'. This is an optional operation, not all DataSeries implementations support it, in which case an UnsupportedOperationException will be thrown. It is provided to allow more efficient access to series that store boolean values as a primitive type (to avoid auto-boxing).

      • getInt

        int getInt(int index)
        Get the element at the specified index as the primitive type 'int'. This is an optional operation, not all DataSeries implementations support it, in which case an UnsupportedOperationException will be thrown. It is provided to allow more efficient access to series that store int values as a primitive type (to avoid auto-boxing).

It is provided to allow more efficient access to series that store long values as a primitive type (to avoid auto-boxing).
